.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH nixling-shell 1 1970-01-01 nixling "nixling CLI"
.SH NAME
shell \- Attach to or manage persistent named guest shells
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBshell\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIARGS\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Attach to or manage persistent named guest shells
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIARGS\fR]
VM name followed by optional shell action and flags; run `nixling shell \-\-help` for forms
.SH EXTRA
Forms:
  nixling shell <vm> [\-\-name NAME] [\-\-force]
  nixling shell <vm> attach [\-\-name NAME] [\-\-force]
  nixling shell <vm> list [\-\-json]
  nixling shell <vm> detach [\-\-name NAME] [\-\-json]
  nixling shell <vm> kill \-\-name NAME [\-\-json]

`nixling shell` opens persistent interactive sessions. Use `nixling vm exec <vm> \-\- <cmd>` for one\-off commands.
